In England, in the seven days to 15 February, there were 73,808 new confirmed cases (131.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 February, there were 100,103 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 26% (26,295 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 20 February is 3,596,965 (6,390.4 cases per 100,000 population).
